	<div id="p185781" class="post row-fluid odd">
	
		<div class="postbody span9">
			

			<div class="author">by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=37087&amp;sid=f74fc8e6aef51741d98139a04cc0be47">Rasadmin</a></strong> &raquo; Mon Oct 01, 2012 12:57 pm </div>

			

			<div class="content">Tried Foggy's way, and it did not work for me.<br />I found another solution elsewhere in these forums and it works for me:<br /><br />sudo nano /etc/lightdm/lightdm.conf<br /><br />In that file, look for:<br />[SeatDefault]<br /><br />and insert this line:<br />xserver-command=X -s 0 dpms<br /><br />My test monitor has been on for a couple of days now  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_e_smile.gif" alt=":-)" title="Smile" /></div>

			

		</div>

		
