	<div id="p215001" class="post row-fluid odd">
	
		<div class="postbody span9">
			

			<div class="author">by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=2570&amp;sid=f74fc8e6aef51741d98139a04cc0be47">jojopi</a></strong> &raquo; Wed Nov 14, 2012 5:27 pm </div>

			

			<div class="content"><blockquote><div><cite>RaTTuS wrote:</cite>the kbd version will stop all console screen blanks</div></blockquote>Putting it another way, kbd will only stop the kernel from blanking the screen when X is not running.<br /><br />And lightdm.conf is only effective if you boot straight into X using that particular display manager.<br /><br />And .xinitrc only works after you log in and run &quot;startx&quot; (or use a display manager that defaults to a user session, and allows .xinitrc instead of .xsession).<br /><br />So you might need all three.  And if you run full-screen non-X programs like XBMC you may need to configure them not to blank as well.</div>

			

		</div>

		
