	<div id="p291931" class="post row-fluid even">
	
		<div class="postbody span9">
			

			<div class="author">by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=52281&amp;sid=f74fc8e6aef51741d98139a04cc0be47">tleland</a></strong> &raquo; Tue Feb 19, 2013 4:08 pm </div>

			

			<div class="content">Only way I've been able to fix this issue is install xscreensaver. To install you need &quot;sudo apt-get install xscreensaver&quot; . In the gui you will now have the &quot;screensaver&quot; option under preferences. Here you can disable the blank screen. Let me know if this makes sense and helps!</div>

			

		</div>

		
