	<div id="p520299" class="post row-fluid even">
	
		<div class="postbody span9">
			

			<div class="author">by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=104013&amp;sid=f74fc8e6aef51741d98139a04cc0be47">carlhage</a></strong> &raquo; Sat Mar 15, 2014 2:22 am </div>

			

			<div class="content">I finally had success disabling blanking with the default Raspbian installation. The xset program is not installed by default, so I did the &quot;sudo apt-get install x11-xserver-utils&quot;. I tested using the &quot;xset q&quot; command. To disable the screen blanking with the default LXDE, edit the file:<br />/etc/xdg/lxsession/LXDE/autostart<br />comment out a xscreensaver command, and add these xset lines<br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: <a href="#" onclick="selectCode(this); return false;">Select all</a></dt><dd><code>#@xscreensaver -no-splash<br />@xset s off<br />@xset -dpms<br />@xset s noblank<br /></code></dd></dl><br /><br />More info at: <a href="http://www.raspberrypi.org/phpBB3/viewtopic.php?f=91&amp;t=57552" class="postlink">http://www.raspberrypi.org/phpBB3/viewtopic.php?f=91&amp;t=57552</a></div>

			

		</div>

		
