			<div class="author">by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=115496&amp;sid=f74fc8e6aef51741d98139a04cc0be47">naumann</a></strong> &raquo; Tue Jul 22, 2014 11:03 am </div>

			

			<div class="content">by Rasadmin worked for me <img src="./images/smilies/icon_e_smile.gif" alt=":-)" title="Smile" /><br /><br />sudo nano /etc/lightdm/lightdm.conf<br /><br />In that file, look for:<br />[SeatDefault]<br /><br />and insert this line:<br />xserver-command=X -s 0 dpms<br /><br />My test monitor has been on for a couple of days now <img src="./images/smilies/icon_e_smile.gif" alt=":-)" title="Smile" /></div>

			

